The paper describes a method for predicting classifications of objects based on a training set, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of Vapnik's support-vector machine suggests a focus on supervised learning, which is often associated with the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The mention of assigning degrees of confidence to predictions and the discussion of possible extensions also suggest a focus on probabilistic modeling, which is often associated with sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The mention of experimental results and the use of continuous probability distributions suggest a focus on computer vision and image processing, which are often associated with sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
